{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "etcd-io/etcd",
      "path": "server/storage/mvcc/kvstore.go",
      "function": "ErrCompacted"
    },
    {
      "repo": "etcd-io/etcd",
      "path": "server/storage/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go",
      "function": "rangeKeys"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The authoritative source of the 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' error is in the etcd-io/etcd upstream repository. The ErrCompacted error constant is defined in server/storage/mvcc/kvstore.go at line 37 as: var ErrCompacted = errors.New(\"mvcc: required revision has been compacted\"). This error is returned by the rangeKeys function in server/storage/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go (starting at line 72) when a client requests a revision that has been garbage-collected by compaction. Specifically, at line 81 of kvstore_txn.go, when the requested revision (rev) is less than the store's compactMainRev (the main revision up to which the store has been compacted), the function returns ErrCompacted. This is the core mechanism that generates the 'etcdserver: mvcc: required revision has been compacted' error seen in Kubernetes apiserver logs. The kubernetes/kubernetes repository's vendored copies under vendor/go.etcd.io/etcd/ contain identical code but are not the authoritative source—they are merely copied snapshots. The Kubernetes error-mapping layer at staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/errors.go translates this raw etcd error into Kubernetes error types but is also not the origin of the error itself. The bug report should cite etcd-io/etcd's server/storage/mvcc/kvstore.go and server/storage/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go as the source components."
}

